BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
OHIO (THE SENATE CONCURRING):
WHEREAS, President Donald Trump recently issued more than 6
one thousand five hundred pardons and commuted the sentences of 7
fourteen individuals in connection with the attack on the United 8
States Capitol on January 6, 2021, when thousands stormed the 9
historic building; and 10
WHEREAS, President Trump commuted the sentences of 11
individuals who were convicted of seditious conspiracy. The 12
President also issued "a full, complete and unconditional pardon 13
to all other individuals convicted of offenses related to events 14
that occurred at or near the United States Capitol on January 6, 15
2021." The group of pardoned individuals includes those who 16
assaulted law enforcement officers; and 17
WHEREAS, The President by issuing those pardons became an 18

